It was what you might call drinking in the Stamford Bridge last chance saloon. 

Mohamed Salah, in all likelihood on his way out of Chelsea, was given one final chance to persuade Jose Mourinho to let him stay.

The fact it was an FA Cup tie against League One opposition in Bradford City, sandwiched between two much more significant and high-profile League Cup games with Liverpool, said everything about the Egyptian’s Chelsea career since he arrived 12 months ago.

He was only on the teamsheet because Mourinho needed to rest his key personnel for Tuesday night’s all-important second leg with the Reds. Plain and simple. In normal circumstances, he probably wouldn’t have made the squad, such are the talents at the manager’s disposal.

