And five minutes later, he cut inside well onto his left foot and curled in a shot that went a couple of inches wide of the post. He was beginning to be genuinely influential.

Then, with the game still delicately-poised at 2-1, it was suddenly all over. The No 17 went up on the board and Salah was replaced by Willian, whom Mourinho hoped would supply the class for a decisive third goal.

There was a smattering of applause for the Egyptian, a few stood in appreciation. Salah, meanwhile, wore the regretful expression of somebody painfully aware all good things must come to an end.

